               <p>SAMUEL STARKEY. I live in <placeName id="t18310407-230-crimeloc1235">Queen-square, Aldersgate-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-230-crimeloc1235" type="placeName" value="Queen-square, Aldersgate-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-230-crimeloc1235" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-230-off1233 t18310407-230-crimeloc1235"></join>. On the 24th of March, between three and four o'clock, a person whom I employ out of doors, sent his son with some work; he rang the bell - the boy answered it; he said he would wait five minutes for an answer - during that time somebody entered the parlour, and took this case and flute; my boy went down, found the parlour door open, and gave an alarm - I went out, and caught the prisoner within five minutes, in Peter's-lane, St. John-street, with the jewel-case under his arm, covered with a handkerchief; I found my flute in his trousers pocket - he was quite a stranger.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-230-person1624">
                  JOHN 
                  ABRAHALL
               <interp inst="t18310407-230-person1624" type="surname" value="ABRAHALL"></interp>
